<p>The below information is available to every website you visit</p>
<h2>General Information</h2>
<p>Your IP address is <b><%= @ip_addr %></b></p>
<p>You are running on <b><%= @browser.os %> <%= @browser.os_version %></b> operating system, with device type <b><%= @browser.form_factor %></b>.</p>
<p>Your browser is <b><%= @browser.browser %> <%= @browser.major_browser_version %></b> which is running engine <b><%= @browser.engine %> <%= @browser.major_engine_version %></b>.</p>

<p>You are in country
  <b><% if @geo.first.country.nil? %>Unknown<% else %><%= @geo.first.country %><% end %></b>, state/county
  <b><% if @geo.first.state.nil? %>Unknown<% else %><%= @geo.first.state %><% end %></b> and city
  <b><% if @geo.first.city.nil? %>Unknown<% else %><%= @geo.first.city %><% end %></b>.</p>
<h2>Other Information</h2>
<p>You followed a link to this site from
  <b><% if @current.referring_domain.nil? %>Unknown<% else %><%= @current.referring_domain %><% end %></b></p>
<p>Your monitor screen size is <b><span id='screen_size'></span></b></p>
<p>Your browser window size is <b><span id='window_size'></span></b></p>
<p>Your monitor color depth is <b><span id='color_depth'></span></b> bit</p>
<% if @tor %>
  <p>You <b>are</b> using Tor</p>
<% else %>
  <p>You are <b>not</b> using Tor</p>
<% end %>

<script>
  document.getElementById("screen_size").innerHTML = screen.width.toString() + 'x' + screen.height.toString();
  document.getElementById("window_size").innerHTML = window.innerWidth.toString() + 'x' + window.innerHeight.toString();
  document.getElementById("color_depth").innerHTML = screen.colorDepth;
</script>
